 <purpose>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of default tolerances for the geometric dimensions of shape elements. </purpose>

 <inscope>
    <li>assigment of default tolerances for the geomentric dimensions of shape elements;</li>
    <li>assignment of default tolerances based on value ranges;</li>
    <li>assignment of default tolerances based on significant digits;</li>
    <li>the association of default tolerances with a product shape;</li>
    <li>default tolerances which are bilateral tolerances;</li>
    <li>default tolerances which are plus or minus tolerances;</li>
    <li>tables of default tolerances;</li>
    <li>default tolerance classes.</li> 
 </inscope>

